# Documentation Standards Rule

## Critical Rules

- All development documentation MUST be placed in the `/development-notes` directory at the project root
- Documentation file names should use kebab-case and include relevant feature name (e.g., `form-validation-system.md`)
- All documentation files MUST follow the established template in `/development-notes/template.md`
- Technical implementation details, design decisions, and development notes should NEVER be placed in `src/` directories
- User-facing documentation (like README, user guides) should be placed at the project root level
- API documentation should be generated using appropriate tools and stored in a dedicated `/docs` directory
- Documentation files must include a date, overview, implementation details, challenges, and solutions
- Code snippets in documentation should use appropriate language tags (e.g., ```typescript, ```html, ```css)
- Documentation files should use Markdown format with proper heading hierarchy
- Documentation must be created/updated as part of the feature implementation process, not after

